COLUMN: Iran will win some short-term battles over the Strait of Hormuz, putting US President Trump over a barrel. But its ability to hold the global economy to ransom will fade as bypass pipelines proliferate. And Iranian officials know it.

@Opinion 

https://t.co/uimMjVJ7bN

India imports over 90% of its crude, more than half its gas — the Strait of Hormuz crisis exposed that dependence in real time. The fix? A two-track energy bet. Oil majors pouring over ₹4 lakh crore into renewables. Ethanol blending hit its 20% target five years early. And now, a new demand thrust from data centres and hyperscalers is reshaping the power sector itself. Traditional energy, new energy, and everything powering the grid in between — CNBC-TV18 decodes where the opportunity, and the risk, really lies.

